org.rakiura.cpn
Class TimedSimulator

java.lang.Object
  org.rakiura.cpn.BasicSimulator
      org.rakiura.cpn.TimedSimulator
All Implemented Interfaces:
Simulator
public class TimedSimulator
extends BasicSimulator

Represents basic timed simulator. Simulated time in this simulator do not run continuously, it steps only when there is no enabled transitions, and it skips to the next smallest token timestamp. All operation and the state of timestamps should be performed via this class methods.

step

public boolean step()
Description copied from class: BasicSimulator
Runs a single step of the simulation. All enabled transitions that can fire simultaneously will be picked from all enabled transitions (see BasicSimulator.occurrence(), and fired in sequence.
This method returns true if there are still more enabled transitions, and false if there is no enabled transition left.

Specified by:
step in interface Simulator
Overrides:
step in class BasicSimulator
Returns:
a boolean value, true if there are still more enabled transitions, and false if there is no enabled transition left.

addDisabledTokens

public void addDisabledTokens()
Special utility method. Adds all previously removed disabled timed tokens. Note, this method to work properly must be proceeded by removeDisabledTokens(). This method is to be used by users manually testing transition enablement. Use it with care.

removeDisabledTokens

public void removeDisabledTokens()
Special utility method. Adds all previously removed disabled timed tokens. Note, this method to work properly must be followed by addDisabledTokens(), otherwise all the disabled tokens will not be present in any of the net Places. This method is to be used by users manually testing transition enablement. Use it with care.
